IMMEDIATE
No .55/1/1/CF-70
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of
Cabinet Affairs)
New Delhi, the 28th June. 1970.
7th Asadha, 1892.
The undersigned is directed to state that with effect from
June 27, 1970 (fore-noon),
(1) Shrimati Indira Gandhi relinquished the office
of Minister of Finance, and assumed the office
of Minister of Home Affairs;
(ii) Shri Fakhruddin Ali Ahmed relinquished the office
of Minister of Industrial Developmant, Internal Trade
and Company Affairs, and assumed the office of Minister
of Food and Agriculture;
(iii) Shri Bali Ram Bhagat relinquished the office of
Minister of Foreign Trade, and assumed the office
of Minister of Steel & Heavy Engineering;
(iv) Shri Y.B. Chavan relinquished the office of Minister
of Home Affairs, and assumed the office of Minister of
Finance;
(v) Shri Jagjivan Ran relinquished the office of Minister
of Food and Agriculture, and assumed the office of
Minister of Defonce;
(vi) Shri Dinesh Singh relinquished the office of Minister
of External Affairs, and assumed the office of Minister
of Industrial Development and Internal Trade;
(vii). Sardar Swaran Singh relinquished the office.of Minister
of Defence, and Steel & Hoavy Engineering, and assumed
the office of Minister of Extornal Affairs;
(viii) Shri Jaganath Rac rolinguished the office of Minister of
State in the, Ministry of Petroleum and Chemicals, and
Mines & Motals, and assumed the office of Minister of
State in the Ministry of Law, and in the Department of
Social Welfare;
(ix) Shri R.K. Khadilkar, Minister of Supply relinquished
the office of Minister of State in the Ministry af
Finance;
( x ) Shri Lalit Narayan Mishra relinquished the office of
Minister of State (Defence Production) in the Ministry
of Defence, and assumed the office of Minister of
Foreign Trade;
Р.Т.О.

(xi)
Shri Krishna Chandra Pant relinquished the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Steel & Heavy
Engineering, and assumed the office of Minister of
State in the Ministry of Home Affairs;
(xii) Shri K.V. Raghunatha Reddy relingquished the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Industrial
Development, Internal Trade and Company Affalrs, and
assumed the office of Minister of Company Affairs;
(xiii) Shri Prakashchand B. Sethi relinquished the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Finance, and
assumed the office of Minister of State (Defence Production)
in the Ministry of Defence;
(xiv) Shri Vidya Charan Shukla relinquished the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Home Affairs, and
assumed the office of Minister of State in the Ministry
of Financey
(xv)
Shri S.C. Jamir relinguished the office of Deputy
Minister in the Ministry of Labour, Employment and
Rehabilitation, and assumed the office of Deputy
Minister in the Ministry of Food, Agriculture, Community
Development and Cooperation;
(xvi) Shri M.R. Krishna relinquished the office of Deputy
Minister in the Ministry of Defence, and assumed the
office of Deputy Minister in the Ministry of Industrial
Development and Internal Trade;
(xvii) Shri Mohammad Yunus Saleem relinquished the office of
Deputy Minister in the Ministry of Law and in the
Department of Social Welfare, and assumed the office
of Deputy Minister in the Ministry of Railways;
(xviii) Shri Bhanu Prakash Singh relinquished the office of
Deputy Minister in the Ministry of .Indus trial
Development, Internal Trade and Company Affairs, and
assumed the office of Deputy Minister in the Ministry
of Petroloum and Chemicals and Mines & Metals.
(R.N. Kalia)
